    "location": "Street, Mongkok",
    "context": "Hong Kong streets can be confusing: overpasses, underground malls, and MTR exits with letters A1 through E. Most locals are happy to help with directions, especially if you try in Cantonese. Saying 唔該 (m4 goi1) before asking is essential politeness.",
    "cultural_note": "Outside a few gridded pockets of Kowloon, Hong Kong refuses to behave like a street grid. The same address might sit on an elevated walkway, down a hillside staircase, or inside a shopping mall that passes straight through a building. Locals navigate by landmarks (opposite the 7-Eleven, up one floor), not compass points or street numbers.",
